modules.description: This module normalizes UTF-encoded strings into specified Unicode forms, handling UTF-8, UTF-16BE, and UTF-16LE encodings directly. It converts malformed Unicode sequences to the replacement character `U+FFFD`. Use it to ensure consistent Unicode representation across different encodings, such as preparing text for comparison or storage.

This module provides Unicode text normalization operations for converting sequences of Unicode characters into canonical forms (`NFD`, `NFC`, `NFKD`, `NFKC`). It processes text incrementally through stateful filters that consume and produce individual Unicode characters, supporting streaming input without requiring full in-memory representation. Concrete use cases include normalizing UTF-8 encoded strings, handling Unicode input in parsers, and ensuring consistent character representation in text processing pipelines.
